I"sq<p><img src="/assets/img/mongodb/mongodb.png" alt="MongoDB Beginner Tutorial" /></p>

<p><a href="https://www.mongodb.com/">MongoDB</a> is a free, open source, multiplatform document-oriented database software, written in the <a href="https://terminalroot.com.br/cpp">C++ language</a>.</p>

<p>Classified as a database program <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NoSQL">NoSQL</a> (generic term that represents non-relational databases, that is, it is not based on the principle that all data are stored in tables).</p>

<p><a href="https://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/MongoDB">MongoDB</a> uses documents similar to <a href="https://www.json.org/">JSON</a> with schematics.</p>

<p>It is developed by <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/company">MongoDB Inc.</a> and published under a combination of the <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html">GNU Affero General Public License</a> and <a href="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache License</a>.</p>

